 Varoma into position, weigh potatoes into it and season with extra salt. Insert Varoma tray and place coated chicken onto it, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>15-18 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<b> or until potatoes and chicken are cooked. Meanwhile, place a frying pan with remaining oil over high heat. Add prosciutto and capers and fry until crispy (approx. 4-5 minutes)."},{"content":"Remove Varoma tray and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl. Place potatoes, fried prosciutto and capers into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and toss to combine. Set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Salad with buttermilk dressing"},{"content":"Place parsley, gherkins, mayonnaise, buttermilk, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Cut reserved chicken into bite-size pieces. Divide lettuce and Parmesan shavings (optional) between serving plates. Arrange chicken and reserved potato mixture onto a serving platter. Drizzle with Buttermilk dressing to serve  (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can substitute chicken tenderloins for chicken breasts, but the cooking times will vary.","To make your own mayonnaise, please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>. Making your own mayonnaise will increase the total time of recipe.","This dressing makes enough to drizzle over salad, chicken and potatoes.","This dish can be served warm or cold."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}